# Console UI

Product-facing console layout and interaction patterns.

## Components

Use **shadcn/ui** for primitives; install missing ones via CLI — see `shadcn-ui.mdc`.

## Layout

- **Header:** shadcn breadcrumb bar — org name (home) + trail + **Settings** and **Account** on the right.
- **Home navigation:** dashboard **cards** link to Members, Applications, Sessions, etc. (not Settings).
- **Content width:** centered column (`max-w-5xl`), not full-bleed on desktop.
- **Drill-down:** breadcrumbs extend in the same header row; app pages use section tabs (Overview, Scopes, Users).

## Copy

- **Do not** add subtitles or explainers under titles when the label is enough.
- **Do** use clear labels on controls (Account, Settings, Members) so the destination is obvious.
- Org name lives in the breadcrumb header only — not repeated in page body.

## Tables

- Row click opens detail; actions column for revoke/remove/disable only.

## Detail pages

- Breadcrumbs for hierarchy; no redundant back buttons.
